parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to a higher risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the seat belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt buckle has broken pieces inside
the seat belt buckle will not buckle
the seat belt buckle has a latching deficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to address the recall can lead to a delay in repairing the defective seat belt buckle, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealership claims to have completed the recall work but did not
dealership claims parts are not available
dealership is not aware of the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering box gear can cause loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: Unusual noise or grinding sound when turning the steering wheel
feeling of tightness or stiffness in the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine oil leak can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil droplets or puddles under the vehicle
oil stains on the garage floor or driveway
low oil pressure warning light illumination
